Energy Recovery Inc. (ERII) , a clean-technology provider for the water, oil and gas industries, won a
contract to retrofit Cadagua SAâ€™s desalination plant in southern
 Spain . No terms were disclosed.  The award is to upgrade and increase energy efficiences of
the Valdelentisco plant in Murcia, which has a potable and
irrigated water production capacity of 140,000 cubic meters a
day, one of the largest desalination plants in Europe, the San
Leandro, California-based company said yesterday in a statement.  The shares of the company, whose technology cuts energy
expenses, have surged 91 percent the past year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
